<li id="cite_note-55"><b><a href="#cite_ref-55" title="">^</a></b> Ehrman 2005, "For the most part, he relied on a mere handful of late medieval manuscripts, which he marked up as if he were copyediting a handwritten copy for the printer.&#160;... Erasmus relied heavily on just one twelfth-century manuscript for the Gospels and another, also of the twelfth century, for the book of Acts and the Epistles.&#160;... For the [last six verses of the] Book of Revelation&#160;... [he] simply took the Latin Vulgate and translated its text back into Greek.&#160;..." (pp 78–79)</li>
