<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Textual_criticism&amp;action=edit&amp;section=37" title="Edit section: Further reading">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Further reading</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>Epp, Eldon J., <i>The Eclectic Method in New Testament Textual Criticism: Solution or Symptom?</i>, The Harvard Theological Review, Vol. 69, No. 3/4 (Jul. - Oct., 1976), pp. 211–257</li>
<li>Aland B., J. Delobel, <i>New Testament Textual Criticism, Exegesis, and Early Church History</i>, Peeters Publishers, 1994.</li>
<li>Hagen, Kenneth, <i>The Bible in the Churches: How Various Christians Interpret the Scriptures</i>, Marquette Studies in Theology, Vol 4; Marquette University Press, 1998, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0874626285" class="internal">ISBN 0-874-62628-5</a></li>
<li>Hodges, Zane C. and Farstad, Arthur L. <i>The Greek New Testament According to the Majority Text with Apparatus</i>, Thomas Nelson; 2nd ed edition (January 1, 1985), <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0840749635" class="internal">ISBN 0-840-74963-5</a></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFHousman1922"><a href="/wiki/Alfred_Edward_Housman" title="Alfred Edward Housman">Housman, A. E.</a> (1922). "<a href="http://cnx.org/content/m11803/latest/" class="external text" title="http://cnx.org/content/m11803/latest/" rel="nofollow">The Application of Thought to Textual Criticism</a>". <i>Proceedings of the Classical Association</i> <b>18</b>: 67–84<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://cnx.org/content/m11803/latest/" class="external free" title="http://cnx.org/content/m11803/latest/" rel="nofollow">http://cnx.org/content/m11803/latest/</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-03-08</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=The+Application+of+Thought+to+Textual+Criticism&amp;rft.jtitle=Proceedings+of+the+Classical+Association&amp;rft.aulast=Housman&amp;rft.aufirst=A.+E.&amp;rft.au=Housman%2C+A.+E.&amp;rft.date=1922&amp;rft.volume=18&amp;rft.pages=67%26ndash%3B84&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fcnx.org%2Fcontent%2Fm11803%2Flatest%2F&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Textual_criticism"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFLove1993">Love, Harold (1993). "section III". <i>Scribal Publication in Seventeenth-Century England</i>. Oxford: Clarendon Press.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=section+III&amp;rft.atitle=Scribal+Publication+in+Seventeenth-Century+England&amp;rft.aulast=Love&amp;rft.aufirst=Harold&amp;rft.au=Love%2C+Harold&amp;rft.date=1993&amp;rft.place=Oxford&amp;rft.pub=Clarendon+Press&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Textual_criticism"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li>Komoszewski, Sawyer and Wallace, (2006), <i>Reinventing Jesus</i>, Kregel Publications, 2006, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780825429828" class="internal">ISBN 978-0825429828</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Bruce_Metzger" title="Bruce Metzger">Metzger</a> &amp; Ehrman, (2005), <i>The text of the New Testament</i>, OUP, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780195161229" class="internal">ISBN 978-0195161229</a></li>
<li>Schiffman, Lawrence H., <i>Reclaiming the Dead Sea Scrolls: The History of Judaism, the Background of Christianity, the Lost Library of Qumran</i>; Jewish Publication Society, 1st ed. 1994, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0827605307" class="internal">ISBN 0-827-60530-7</a></li>
<li>Soulen, Richard N. and Soulen, R. Kendall, <i>Handbook of Biblical Criticism</i>; Westminster John Knox Press; 3 edition (October 2001), <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0664223141" class="internal">ISBN 0-664-22314-1</a></li>
</ul>
<p><a name="External_links" id="External_links"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Textual_criticism&amp;action=edit&amp;section=38" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">External links</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://openscriptures.org/prototypes/manuscript-comparator/" class="external text" title="http://openscriptures.org/prototypes/manuscript-comparator/" rel="nofollow">Manuscript Comparator</a> — allows two or more New Testament manuscript editions to be compared in side-by-side and unified views (similar to <a href="/wiki/Diff" title="Diff">diff</a> output)</li>
<li><a href="http://www-user.uni-bremen.de/~wie/TCG/index.html" class="external text" title="http://www-user.uni-bremen.de/~wie/TCG/index.html" rel="nofollow">A detailed discussion of the textual variants in the Gospels</a> (covering about 1200 variants on 2000 pages)</li>
<li><a href="http://www-user.uni-bremen.de/~wie/texte/Papyri-list.html" class="external text" title="http://www-user.uni-bremen.de/~wie/texte/Papyri-list.html" rel="nofollow">A complete list of all New Testament Papyri</a> with link to images</li>
<li><a href="http://itsee.bham.ac.uk/iohannes/byzantine/index.html" class="external text" title="http://itsee.bham.ac.uk/iohannes/byzantine/index.html" rel="nofollow">An Electronic Edition</a> of The Gospel According to John in the Byzantine Tradition</li>
<li><a href="http://www.skypoint.com/~waltzmn/" class="external text" title="http://www.skypoint.com/~waltzmn/" rel="nofollow">A Site Inspired By The Encyclopedia of New Testament Textual Criticism</a></li>
<li><a href="http://rjohara.net/darwin/files/bmcr" class="external text" title="http://rjohara.net/darwin/files/bmcr" rel="nofollow">An example of cladistics applied to textual criticism</a></li>
<li><a href="http://groups.yahoo.com/group/textualcriticism/" class="external text" title="http://groups.yahoo.com/group/textualcriticism/" rel="nofollow">Mailing list textual criticism</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.tcg.iphpbb3.com" class="external text" title="http://www.tcg.iphpbb3.com" rel="nofollow">Forum Textual Criticism</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.skypoint.com/~waltzmn/CriticalEds.html#HF" class="external text" title="http://www.skypoint.com/~waltzmn/CriticalEds.html#HF" rel="nofollow">A book review for Hodges &amp; Farstad</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.aramaicpeshitta.com" class="external text" title="http://www.aramaicpeshitta.com" rel="nofollow">Aramaic Bible Textual Criticism</a></li>
<li><a href="http://evangelicaltextualcriticism.blogspot.com" class="external text" title="http://evangelicaltextualcriticism.blogspot.com" rel="nofollow">Evangelical Textual Criticism Blog</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.laparola.net/greco/" class="external text" title="http://www.laparola.net/greco/" rel="nofollow">New Testament Manuscripts</a> (listing of the manuscript evidence for more than 11000 variants in the New Testament)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/File:Wikisource-logo.svg" class="image" title="Wikisource-logo.svg"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4c/Wikisource-logo.svg/15px-Wikisource-logo.svg.png" width="15" height="16" border="0" /></a>&#160;<cite style="font-style:normal" class="book"><a href="http://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Catholic_Encyclopedia_(1913)/Lower_Criticism" class="external text" title="http://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Catholic_Encyclopedia_(1913)/Lower_Criticism" rel="nofollow">"Lower Criticism"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/Catholic_Encyclopedia" title="Catholic Encyclopedia">Catholic Encyclopedia</a></i>. New York: Robert Appleton Company. 1913<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Catholic_Encyclopedia_(1913)/Lower_Criticism" class="external free" title="http://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Catholic_Encyclopedia_(1913)/Lower_Criticism" rel="nofollow">http://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Catholic_Encyclopedia_(1913)/Lower_Criticism</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Lower+Criticism&amp;rft.atitle=%5B%5BCatholic+Encyclopedia%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=1913&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Robert+Appleton+Company&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fen.wikisource.org%2Fwiki%2FCatholic_Encyclopedia_%281913%29%2FLower_Criticism&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Textual_criticism"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><a href="http://www.skypoint.com/members/waltzmn/Stemma.html" class="external text" title="http://www.skypoint.com/members/waltzmn/Stemma.html" rel="nofollow">Stemma and Stemmatics</a></li>
<li><a href="http://w3.uniroma1.it/cogfil/ecdotica.html" class="external text" title="http://w3.uniroma1.it/cogfil/ecdotica.html" rel="nofollow">Stemmatics and Information Theory</a></li>
</ul>
